# 3ssaf_E-Commerce API DocumentationThis document describes the endpoints in the `3ssaf_E-Commerce` API collection.> Note: Response bodies in this document are inferred examples based on endpoint names and request structure. They should be verified against the running backend before publishing as final docs.---## Base URL```bash{{baseUrl}}
Example:

https://api.example.com
Authentication
Most protected endpoints will likely require:

Authorization: Bearer <token>Content-Type: application/jsonAccept: application/json
Common inferred error response:

{    "success": false,    "message": "Unauthorized"}
Response Format Convention
A common inferred success format used in this document:

{    "success": true,    "message": "Operation completed         successfully",    "data": {}}
A common inferred validation error format:

{    "success": false,    "message": "Validation failed",    "errors": {        "field": [            "This field is required"        ]    }}
Auth
1. Signup
Method: POST
Endpoint: /auth/signup

Request Body
{    "name": "Ahmed Wageh",    "email": "ahmed@example.com",    "password": "StrongPassword123",    "phone": "01000000000"}
Example Success Response
{    "success": true,    "message": "User registered         successfully",    "data": {        "id": "user_id",        "name": "Ahmed Wageh",        "email": "ahmed@example.com",        "phone": "01000000000",        "role": "user"    },    "token": "jwt_token_here"}
Example Error Response
{    "success": false,    "message": "User already exists"}
2. Login
Method: POST
Endpoint: /auth/login

Request Body
{    "email": "ahmed@example.com",    "password": "StrongPassword123"}
Example Success Response
{    "success": true,    "message": "Login successful",    "data": {        "user": {            "id": "user_id",            "name": "Ahmed Wageh",            "email": "ahmed@example.            "role": "user"        },        "token": "jwt_token_here"    }                com",}
Example Error Response
{    "success": false,    "message": "Invalid email or         password"}
3. Verify Email
Method: GET
Endpoint: /auth/verify-email/:token

Path Params
Name	Type	Description
token	string	Email verification token
Example Success Response
{    "success": true,    "message": "Email verified         successfully"}
Example Error Response
{    "success": false,    "message": "Invalid or expired         verification token"}
4. Resend Verification
Method: POST
Endpoint: /auth/resend-verification

Request Body
{    "email": "ahmed@example.com"}
Example Success Response
{    "success": true,    "message": "Verification email         sent successfully"}
5. Forgot Password
Method: POST
Endpoint: /auth/forgot-password

Request Body
{    "email": "ahmed@example.com"}
Example Success Response
{    "success": true,    "message": "Password reset email         sent successfully"}
6. Reset Password
Method: POST
Endpoint: /auth/reset-password/:token

Path Params
Name	Type	Description
token	string	Reset password token
Request Body
{    "password":     "confirmPassword":         "NewStrongPassword123"        "NewStrongPassword123",}
Example Success Response
{    "success": true,    "message": "Password reset         successfully"}
